# Build Versioning

The game shows a build badge in the bottom-right of the screen (e.g. `Dev V0.2.0a`).
The single source of truth is `GAME_VERSION` in `apps/client/src/version.ts`.

## Rule: bump it whenever you ship a change

After making a meaningful code/content change, increment `GAME_VERSION` to reflect it.
Format: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH<build>` (build letter optional).

| Change type | What to bump | Example |
|-------------|--------------|---------|
| Big milestone / breaking rework | MAJOR (reset minor+patch) | `0.2.0a` → `1.0.0` |
| New feature or system | MINOR (reset patch) | `0.2.0a` → `0.3.0` |
| Fix, tweak, balance, polish | PATCH | `0.2.0a` → `0.2.1` |
| Quick same-version iteration | build letter | `0.2.0` → `0.2.0a` → `0.2.0b` |

## How

Edit only the one line in `apps/client/src/version.ts`:

```typescript
export const GAME_VERSION = '0.3.0';
```

Do not hardcode the version anywhere else — import `GAME_VERSION` / `VERSION_LABEL`
from `version.ts` instead.
